Summary: This update focuses on hardening server security and administrative control. We have removed the experimental Premium Auto-Login features to ensure maximum stability and zero data loss, while introducing powerful brute-force protection and external integrations.
ğŸ”’ Brute-Force Protection (Account Locking)
Automatic Locking: If a player is kicked 3 times (default) for entering the wrong password, their account is permanently LOCKED.
Behavior: Locked players can join but cannot move, chat, or execute commands. They will see a "Blocked" screen.
Resolution: Admins must use /pureauth unlock <player> to restore access.
ğŸ¤– Captcha System
New players must enter a random 5-character alphanumeric code during registration to prevent bot attacks.
Configurable in config.yml.
ğŸ”” Discord Webhook Integration
The plugin can now send alerts to a Discord channel for:
Failed login attempts (Kicks).
Account Lockouts.
Administrative actions (Unregister, Force Login, Password Changes).
ğŸ›¡ï¸ Safe Mode
Added a safe_mode switch in the config. When enabled, sensitive admin commands (like changing passwords or unregistering players) are blocked in-game and can only be executed from the Server Console.
ğŸŒ Localization
Full support for English (EN) and Polish (PL). Switch languages instantly in the config.
ğŸ› ï¸ Admin Tools
New: /pureauth unlock <player> - Unblocks a locked account.
New: /pureauth register <player> <password> - Manually register a player.
Improved: /pureauth stats - Displays detailed configuration status.
